race.comment: LET'S TALK (3) got the job done two back in good fashion before rising in grade last start and feeling the pinch late. ZJP takes the ride now, getting him in nicely at the weights. Has the speed to roll across from out wide and can be in this for a very long way. AIN'T NO OTHER MAN (1) has led them up his past couple, leading and finishing 1L off the winner most recently in stronger company. It was a better run however, finishing 2.7L off LET'S TALK two back at Ascot. Inside draw this time suits better and he can make an impression. SNIPPY WHICH (5) has been running on from the back of the pack in recent efforts and gets a chance to sit much closer today. He'll find this easier than recent efforts as well and Nottle's claim comes in handy. Can go close. SNOW PRINCE (4) is building nicely this time in work and is not to be discounted. UNIVERSAL PLAYBOY (6) is better than he showed last time out and will be hard to catch if he can find the front.
